reviews.review_text: FOB AUD Forever Every show I try to just find the FOB AUD. I switch back and forth checking other AUD’s especially Charlie Miller transfers and hear the differences in sections of the audience, but 9/10 times I end up going back to whatever the FOB source is. The sound is so clean, mix of crowd, music is full, and the vocals normally don’t have that sound of tin. Could it just be mics and tapes and other gear, sure, but unless you have a copy of the physical tape, I can’t judge it properly. For my money, find the Front Of Board recordings, plus, if you think about it, these guys risked a little extra getting these FOB recordings, so out of respect for their effort at least it’s pretty cool to hear this stuff. If you’re looking for the best of this specific show, do I need to go on? This is it.
